A is a virtual table based on the result set of a SELECT query. They do not store data
themselves, but provide a way to present the data from one or more tables in a customized
manner. Multiple views present different subsets of the data to different users, with the data
being presented in different ways according to the user’s needs.
There are several advantages of using views:
Views can encapsulate complex queries, simplifying the process
for users to query data without needing to understand the underlying SQL.
Views can present data in a consistent manner, even if the underlying
The database schema can be changed without affecting the user views.
Views can increase performance by simplifying complex queries, by
abstracting join operations into a single reusable object (the view).
